RetailNova Sales Analysis Project
This project is a complete data analysis of a retail business. I used Python for cleaning data, SQL for deep analysis, and Power BI to create a visual dashboard.

Project Overview
The goal of this project is to help "RetailNova" understand their sales, identify their best customers, and find ways to increase profit across different store locations.

What I Did:
1. Data Cleaning & Exploration (Python)
Used Pandas to clean raw customer and sales files.
Fixed missing data and corrected dates.
Created charts with Seaborn and Matplotlib to see initial sales trends.

2. Advanced Analysis (SQL)
Wrote complex queries to find the Top 5 most profitable customers.
Calculated monthly profit trends for the last two years.
Identified which products are returned most often so the business can improve quality.
Created Indexes to make the database search much faster.

3. Interactive Dashboard (Power BI)
Built a visual report to track Revenue, Profit, and Returns.
Added filters to see performance by Region (North, South, East, West).
Compared different store types like Flagship stores vs. Online sales.

Key Skills Used:
Python: Data Wrangling & Visualization.
SQL: Joins, Window Functions, and Database Optimization.
Power BI: Data Modeling and Dashboard Design.
